
üß© 1. Stereotype Annotations (for Beans/Components)

These define what kind of Spring-managed component a class is:

| Annotation        | Description                                                                                       |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@Component`      | A generic Spring-managed bean.                                                                    |
| `@Service`        | A **service layer** bean (business logic). Same as `@Component`, just more specific semantically. |
| `@Repository`     | A **DAO (Data Access Object)** bean for database operations. Enables **exception translation**.   |
| `@Controller`     | Marks a **Spring MVC controller** class (for web requests).                                       |
| `@RestController` | Combines `@Controller` + `@ResponseBody` ‚Üí used for **REST APIs**.                                |



‚öôÔ∏è 2. Dependency Injection Annotations
Annotation	Description


@Autowired	-- Automatically injects dependencies (by type).

private final name -- should have @AllArgsConstructor.


üßæ 3. Web and REST API Annotations

| Annotation                                                                      | Description                                                                       |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@RequestMapping`                                                               | Maps HTTP requests to controller methods (for all methods: GET, POST, etc.).      |
| `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`, `@PutMapping`, `@DeleteMapping`, `@PatchMapping` | Shorthand for specific HTTP methods.                                              |
| `@PathVariable`                                                                 | Binds a **URI path variable** to a method parameter.                              |
| `@RequestParam`                                                                 | Binds **query parameters** (e.g. `?id=1`).                                        |
| `@RequestBody`                                                                  | Maps the **body of the request** (usually JSON) to a Java object.                 |
| `@ResponseBody`                                                                 | Converts the returned Java object to JSON (used internally in `@RestController`). |
| `@CrossOrigin`                                                                  | Enables **CORS** (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) for REST endpoints.              |



üóÑÔ∏è 4. JPA and Database Annotations

| Annotation                                             | Description                                                                                  |
| ------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@Entity`                                              | Marks a class as a **JPA entity** (maps to a database table).                                |
| `@Table(name = "table_name")`                          | Specifies the table name for an entity.                                                      |
| `@Id`                                                  | Marks the **primary key** field.                                                             |
| `@GeneratedValue(strategy = ...)`                      | Specifies how the ID is generated (`AUTO`, `IDENTITY`, `SEQUENCE`).                          |
| `@Column(name = "col_name")`                           | Customizes a database column.                                                                |
| `@OneToOne`, `@OneToMany`, `@ManyToOne`, `@ManyToMany` | Define **relationships** between entities.                                                   |
| `@JoinColumn`                                          | Specifies the **foreign key** column.                                                        |
| `@Transactional`                                       | Ensures that a method runs in a **transaction** ‚Äî commits on success, rolls back on failure. |

