üß† 5. Boilerplate Reduction (Core)

| Annotation           | Description                                                                                             | Example                             |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `@Getter`            | Generates getter methods for all fields.                                                                | `getName()`                         |
| `@Setter`            | Generates setter methods for all fields.                                                                | `setName(String name)`              |
| `@ToString`          | Generates a `toString()` method including all fields.                                                   | `"Student(name=John, age=20)"`      |
| `@EqualsAndHashCode` | Generates `equals()` and `hashCode()` methods.                                                          | Used in comparisons or sets/maps.   |
| `@Data`              | Combines `@Getter`, `@Setter`, `@ToString`, `@EqualsAndHashCode`, and `@RequiredArgsConstructor`.       | Commonly used in DTOs and Entities. |
| `@Value`             | Makes class **immutable** ‚Üí all fields `private final`, generates getters, constructor, and no setters. | Like a record class.                |


üèóÔ∏è 6. Constructors

| Annotation                 | Description                                                           |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@NoArgsConstructor`       | Generates a **no-argument constructor** (`public Student() {}`)       |
| `@AllArgsConstructor`      | Generates a constructor with **all fields**.                          |
| `@RequiredArgsConstructor` | Generates a constructor for **final** and **`@NonNull`** fields only. |


üîí 7. Validation Annotations (from javax.validation or jakarta.validation)

| Annotation                           | Description                                          |
| ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `@NotNull`, `@NotEmpty`, `@NotBlank` | Validate that a field is not null/empty.             |
| `@Size(min, max)`                    | Limits the size of a string/collection.              |
| `@Min`, `@Max`                       | Numeric range validation.                            |
| `@Email`                             | Validates email format.                              |
| `@Pattern(regexp = "...")`           | Validates a regex pattern.                           |
| `@Valid`                             | Used on method parameters to **trigger validation**. |




